Heading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Leontine martyrs</h1>\n\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub2\"></div>\n\t\t\n\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#searchInput\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Leontine Martyrs</b> were a group of people who were killed after a long period of captivity in Persia. They were executed by the order of King <a href=\"/wiki/Yazdegerd_II\" title=\"Yazdegerd II\">Yazdegerd II</a> in 455, five years after the insurrection led by <a href=\"/wiki/Mamikonian#Vartan_Mamikonian\" title=\"Mamikonian\">Vartan Mamikonian</a>. The group is named after Leontius of Vanand (In Armenian \u054d\u0578\u0582\u0580\u0562 \u0542\u0587\u0578\u0576\u0564, pronounced \"Surb Ghevond\"), the most senior of the religious group.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Martyrs\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Martyrs</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Leontius_of_Vanand\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Leontius of Vanand</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Joseph_I_of_Armenia\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Joseph I of Armenia</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Sahak_of_Syunik_Rshtuni\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sahak of Syunik Rshtuni</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Tatik_of_Basen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Tatik of Basen</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Mushegh\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Mushegh</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Arshen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Arshen</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Samuel\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Samuel</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Survivors\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Survivors</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Abraham_of_Arazd\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Abraham of Arazd</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#Veneration\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Veneration</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Martyrs\">Martyrs</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Martyrs\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"box-Expand_section plainlinks metadata ambox mbox-small-left ambox-content\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"[icon]\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"20\" height=\"14\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/30px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"31\" /></a></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This section <b>needs expansion</b>&#32;with: biographies of the names. <small>You can help by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=\">adding to it</a>.</small>  <small class=\"date-container\"><i>(<span class=\"date\">June 2019</span>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Leontius_of_Vanand\">Leontius of Vanand</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Leontius of Vanand\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>A high level priest also known as St. Ghevond (in Armenian \u054d\u0578\u0582\u0580\u0562 \u0542\u0587\u0578\u0576\u0564)\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Joseph_I_of_Armenia\">Joseph I of Armenia</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Joseph I of Armenia\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Joseph I of Armenia or St. Hovsep I (in Armenian \u054d\u0562. \u0540\u0578\u057e\u057d\u0565\u0583 \u0531 \u0540\u0578\u0572\u0578\u0581\u0574\u0565\u0581\u056b), catholicos of Armenia (437\u2013452)\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sahak_of_Syunik_Rshtuni\">Sahak of Syunik Rshtuni</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Sahak of Syunik Rshtuni\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Sahak of Syunik Rshtuni (in Armenian \u054d\u0561\u0570\u0561\u056f \u0565\u057a\u057d. \u054c\u0577\u057f\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0575\u0561\u0581) - a  bishop\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Tatik_of_Basen\">Tatik of Basen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Tatik of Basen\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Tatik of Basen (in Armenian \u0532\u0561\u057d\u0565\u0576\u0575\u0561\u0581 \u0539\u0561\u0569\u056b\u056f \u0565\u057a\u056b\u057d\u056f\u0578\u057a\u0578\u057d) - a bishop\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Mushegh\">Mushegh</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Mushegh\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Mushe or Mushegh (in Armenian \u0544\u0578\u0582\u0577\u0565\u0572 \u0584\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0575) - A priest\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Arshen\">Arshen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Arshen\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Arshen (in Armenian \u0531\u0580\u0577\u0565\u0576 \u0565\u0580\u0565\u0581) - a priest\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Samuel\">Samuel</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: Samuel\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Samuel (in Armenian \u054d\u0561\u0574\u0578\u0582\u0567\u056c \u0584\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0575) - a priest\n</p><p>Plus a number of deacons\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Survivors\">Survivors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Survivors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Abraham_of_Arazd\">Abraham of Arazd</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Abraham of Arazd\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Abraham of Arazd was an <a href=\"/wiki/Armenia\" title=\"Armenia\">Armenian</a> priest and a disciple of the Leontine martyrs. Like his teachers, he was subjected to prolonged <a href=\"/wiki/Torture\" title=\"Torture\">torture</a>, but unlike them, was eventually set free. \n</p><p>He afterward left society to become a <a href=\"/wiki/Hermit\" title=\"Hermit\">hermit</a>, remaining one until his death in the 5th century. He is regarded as a <a href=\"/wiki/Saint\" title=\"Saint\">saint</a> by the <a href=\"/wiki/Armenian_Church\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armenian Church\">Armenian Church</a>, with a <a href=\"/wiki/Feast_day\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Feast day\">feast day</a> of December 20.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Veneration\">Veneration</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: Veneration\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>St. Ghevond the Priest and His Companions are commemorated as <a href=\"/wiki/Saint\" title=\"Saint\">saints</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/Armenian_Apostolic_Church\" title=\"Armenian Apostolic Church\">Armenian Apostolic Church</a>. The day of the Feast of St. Ghevond the Priest and His Companions is July 31. It is also considered the day of the clergy in the Armenian Church and their office is celebrated on the Tuesday after the western <a href=\"/wiki/Sexagesima\" title=\"Sexagesima\">Sexagesima</a>, as they are regarded as the <a href=\"/wiki/Patron_saint\" title=\"Patron saint\">patron saints</a> of the Armenian clergy.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Leontine_martyrs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Holweck, F. G. <i>A Biographical Dictionary of the Saints</i>. St. Louis, MO: B. Herder Book Co. 1924.</li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Saint-stub-icon.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Saint-stub-icon.jpg/25px-Saint-stub-icon.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Saint-stub-icon.jpg/38px-Saint-stub-icon.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Saint-stub-icon.jpg/50px-Saint-stub-icon.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"110\" data-file-height=\"110\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about a saint is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=L